-- MovieTickets.com Reports ‘Hunger Games’ Set a Presale Record
-- B y   R o b   G o l u m
-- 2012-03-23T15:21:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-23/movietickets-com-reports-hunger-games-set-a-presale-record.html
MovieTickets.com, the service owned
by theater chains and studio owners, said “The Hunger Games”
became the company’s top advance seller for a non-sequel film,
surpassing “Twilight.”  The picture from  Lions Gate Entertainment Corp. (LGF)  sold out
2,500 screenings, including 1,400 that were held at midnight,
the company said today in an e-mailed statement.  MovieTickets.com is owned by AMC Entertainment,  Hollywood
Media Corp. (HOLL) ,  National Amusements , Cineplex Entertainment, Marcus
Theatres, Viacom Inc. and  Time Warner Inc. (TWX) , according to the
company’s website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Golum at 
 rgolum@bloomberg.net  